    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The aim of this study was to estimate the immunogenic effect of mRNA vaccine against SARS-CoV-2. This study included 510 participants who received mRNA vaccine. The measurement of anti-Covid-19 antibodies was performed using the Abbott SARS-CoV-2 IgG quantitative assay (Abbott). Overall, mean title of anti-Spike antibodies was 19319.2\u00b11787.5 AU/ml. Vaccination induced a robust immunogenic response in previous infected with SARS-CoV-2 compared. Additionally, individuals that were asymptomatic after vaccination produced lower levels of antibodies compared to feverish individuals. In conclusion, remarkable high level of anti-Spike Covid-19 antibodies was found after vaccination.</jats:p>",
